# Content section tree navigation

When a tab renders **two or more major content panels** (separate cards or regions), use **`ContentSectionTreeNav`** from `@/components/ui/content-section-tree-nav` so users switch sections without stacking every panel on one long page.

Read `.agent/knowledge/ui-content-sections.md` for full rules. Do **not** use pill-style `TabsList` for this level of navigation.

- Centered tree switcher (stem + branch labels as text links)
- One panel visible at a time
- Shared filters stay **above** the tree nav
